ssanity is a way to verify that the intended flags to be set or unset in the termios structure are indeed set or unset.

Terminal programming is very platform-dependant (so sayeth Stevens and Rago in Advanced Programming in the Unix Environment) so your mileage may vary. This works fine in Ubuntu 12.04.

Massive hat tip to Tod E. Kurt (http://todbot.com/blog/) for having the only readable example of serial communication with an Arduino.
